<div id="review_952820568" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/952820568" />
    <a title="GymGuy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5850785-gymguy"><img alt="GymGuy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1354080751p2/5850785.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/952820568?book_show_action=true">May 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="GymGuy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="GymGuy" href="/user/show/5850785-gymguy">GymGuy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5850785-gymguy?shelf=action-thriller">action-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5850785-gymguy?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5850785-gymguy?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5850785-gymguy?shelf=gothic">gothic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer952820568" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6657081111202217641">Great story with lots of subplots with significant touches of horror, occult and paranormal. There was not much legal/courtroom drama to it, however, which I found disappointing. I enjoyed the reality of the characters. Great gothic threads running throughout: the coldness of the air, rain, Natasha&apos;s home, the mother, the Doberman, I could go on-and-on.</span>
  <span id="freeText6657081111202217641" style="display:none">Great story with lots of subplots with significant touches of horror, occult and paranormal. There was not much legal/courtroom drama to it, however, which I found disappointing. I enjoyed the reality of the characters. Great gothic threads running throughout: the coldness of the air, rain, Natasha's home, the mother, the Doberman, I could go on-and-on.</span>
