        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3808956096" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8791741999052059090">I delved into the second book in Scott Pratt&apos;s Joe Dillard Series - &quot;In Good Faith&quot; - after enjoying his first book, An Innocent Client. A great lover of the mystery genre with court battles sprinkled throughout, &quot;In Good Faith&quot; did not disappoint me. I love the way the author doesn&apos;t focus on just one case in the story because that would not be the reality of a real lawyer - defense attorney or DA. You won&apos;t be able to put the book down as you dig deeper through the pages, and you will learn mo</span>
  <span id="freeText8791741999052059090" style="display:none">I delved into the second book in Scott Pratt's Joe Dillard Series - "In Good Faith" - after enjoying his first book, An Innocent Client. A great lover of the mystery genre with court battles sprinkled throughout, "In Good Faith" did not disappoint me. I love the way the author doesn't focus on just one case in the story because that would not be the reality of a real lawyer - defense attorney or DA. You won't be able to put the book down as you dig deeper through the pages, and you will learn more and more about how the legal system works - and doesn't!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8791741999052059090" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
