              <span id="reviewTextContainer1566631856" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10837328787697665143">Book #2 in the legal mystery/thriller series by author Scott Pratt deals with ritual murder and the occult in Tennessee. Falling somewhat short of his debut book &quot; An Innocent Client&quot;, Pratt may have jumped the shark by embodying the evil antagonist with supernatural powers. Regardless, it was an interesting and enjoyable read mostly because I liked the development of his protagonist attorney, now Prosecutor, Joe Dillard and his family.</span>
  <span id="freeText10837328787697665143" style="display:none">Book #2 in the legal mystery/thriller series by author Scott Pratt deals with ritual murder and the occult in Tennessee. Falling somewhat short of his debut book " An Innocent Client", Pratt may have jumped the shark by embodying the evil antagonist with supernatural powers. Regardless, it was an interesting and enjoyable read mostly because I liked the development of his protagonist attorney, now Prosecutor, Joe Dillard and his family.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10837328787697665143" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


