<div id="review_1456662253" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1456662253" />
    <a title="Marleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1616365-marleen"><img alt="Marleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643749125p2/1616365.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1456662253?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marleen" href="/user/show/1616365-marleen">Marleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18815922-in-good-faith">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1616365-marleen?shelf=scott-pratt">scott-pratt</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1456662253" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4205850970471035119">In Good Faith is the second Joe Dillard book and the more I get to know this character, the more I like him. What I appreciate best is that he is a pretty normal guy with a normal family life. There isn’t any animosity in his personal life and that is a rather refreshing premise. As for his professional life – first working as a criminal defense lawyer for a decade and then switching to being a prosecutor, now that’s not easy feat. What is so likable about Joe is that he’s a person with integrit</span>
  <span id="freeText4205850970471035119" style="display:none">In Good Faith is the second Joe Dillard book and the more I get to know this character, the more I like him. What I appreciate best is that he is a pretty normal guy with a normal family life. There isn’t any animosity in his personal life and that is a rather refreshing premise. As for his professional life – first working as a criminal defense lawyer for a decade and then switching to being a prosecutor, now that’s not easy feat. What is so likable about Joe is that he’s a person with integrity – no matter what side he’s on.<br />In this second installment, Joe’s questioning his beliefs, more specifically his religious convictions. It’s not life altering, but being confronted with these murderers who believe in satanism, Joe's confronted with strange happenings in his daily life. Foremost these young murderers are mentally ill and socially lost. It’s so sickening to read how empty these criminals are on the inside. I wasn’t particularly taken with the satanic component of the story, but overall this was an enjoyable read. I look forward to the next book. ***3,5*** stars<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4205850970471035119" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


